      "id": "74eb542237eb7171",
      "text": "Where there are standards, there are usually several of them to standardize the same thing, process, method. Then, users complain and start to call for their harmonization. This demand is easy to understand. Just as it is easy to understand that the proliferation of standards is a naturally occuring process. From the Big Bang, to the formation of stars and galaxies, living systems, communities, cities, economic powers: things clump together and diversify and branch out, then clump together and at a certain point things emerge with new qualities at a new level."
    },
